SUMMARY:Art Conversation  Remixed: Florida Artists Look at Art History
LOCATION:1505 N Nebraska Tampa \, FL 33605 United States
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an engaging and interactive discussion at the Robe
 rt W. Saunders\, Sr. Public Library. Joanna Robotham\, Curator of Modern a
 nd Contemporary Art at the Tampa Museum of Art\, will present a talk on Fl
 orida artists Pepe Mar\, Mernet Larsen\, Purvis Young\, and Theo Wujcik. I
 nspired by art history\, the artists create unique artworks that demonstra
 te the influence of Old Master painters\, the Russian Avant-Garde\, the Im
 pressionists\, and 20th-century trailblazers. This presentation will highl
 ight how contemporary artists have created a union between the past and th
 e present in their works of art. Pepe Mar\, Mernet Larsen\, Purvis Young\,
  and Theo Wujciks art are part of the Tampa Museum of Arts permanent colle
 ction. They are featured artists in the poster exhibition Made in Florida\
 , on view across the Hillsborough County Library system. \n\nPermalink: ht
 tps://www.tampa.gov/node/190821
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/190821
END:VEVENT
